<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMPARING FOREIGN AND U.S. AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I got a big laugh while reading Koblosh's letter detailing the problems he has 
had with his 1985 Dodge. May I present the following problems I have 
experienced with my 1983 Toyota pickup truck: 
</P>
<P>
Four brake failures; 2 headlight replacements less than 1 year after purchase; 
total brake failure; refusal to repair damaged right wing window while under 
warranty; need for 4 new tires less than 2 years after purchase (less than 
25,000 miles driven); replacement of timing chain; cracked bearing; total 
engine failure -- 4 years after purchase; battery cable failure; replacement of 
entire fuel pump system. 
</P>
<P>
I could go on, but I think I've made my point. Do you think I'll ever buy 
anything made by Toyota? No way! 
</P>
<P>
RONALD KERNS 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
