<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMPARING FOREIGN AND U.S. AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have been the sole owner of a 1985 Pontiac Grand Am. 
</P>
<P>
In its service to me of over 53,000 miles I had but one problem, with the fuel 
pump. Even the tires, battery and brakes lasted nearly 50,000 miles; still 
going on the original hoses and belts. The paint job is phenomenal, still shiny 
and new looking. In my 63 years I have had at least 6 U.S. cars, bought new, 
some driven well over 100,000 miles with very few problems. If I didn't love my 
present car so much I'd buy a new domestic car. 
</P>
<P>
EARLE B. EMERY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
