<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAL LUTHERAN WIN STREAK ENDS AT 5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE In another women's game: Antelope Valley 63, C 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kim Eproson and the Cal State Los Angeles women's basketball team broke Cal 
Lutheran's school-record five-game winning streak with a convincing 80-66 
victory Friday night at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Eproson came off the bench to pour in a game-high 25 points, 23 in the second 
half, to help Cal State L. A. (6-7) break a six-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
"(Eproson) was just amazing," Cal Lutheran Coach Norm Chung said. 
</P>
<P>
"We couldn't stop her. We didn't let her get any shots simply standing 
stationary. We made her work for her shots. She just didn't miss." 
</P>
<P>
Not exactly, but pretty close. 
</P>
<P>
Eproson made 10 of 18 field-goal attempts, mostly on long-distance bombs, and 
she sank five of six free throws. 
</P>
<P>
The Regals (9-3) led, 46-45, with 12 minutes, 46 seconds to play before Eproson 
went to work. 
</P>
<P>
The 5-foot-7 junior guard scored the Eagles' next 10 points in a 4:26 span, all 
on outside shooting to give Cal State L. A. a 55-50 advantage. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran pulled to within a point, 61-60, with 4:16 to play when Joy Fuller 
made a layup. But Cal State L. A. went on a 14-1 blitz with Eproson scoring 10 
of the 14 to seal the win. 
</P>
<P>
Lori Thompson scored 16 points and Kelly O'Brien added 12 and 15 rebounds for 
Cal State L. A. 
</P>
<P>
Brenda Lee led Cal Lutheran with 16 points, 12 rebounds and five steals. Leslie 
Stevens chipped in with 12. 
</P>
<P>
In the first half, Cal State L. A. led, 20-9, but Cal Lutheran closed to 34-32 
by halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State L. A. hit 52% from the field in the second half on 16-of-31 shooting 
while limiting Cal Lutheran to 34% (13 of 31). KIRBY LEE In another women's 
game: Antelope Valley 63, Citrus 49 -- Antelope Valley improved to 2-0 in the 
Foothill Conference with a victory at Citrus. Forward Denese Prince led 
Antelope Valley (7-7) with 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds. Susan Hervey had 
a team-high 15 rebounds.MEN West L. A. 89, Canyons 88 -- Holding a one-point 
lead with 12 seconds remaining, West L. A. missed the front end of two 
different one-and-ones but managed to grab the offensive rebound both times and 
deny Canyons an opportunity for a come-from-behind win in a Western State 
Conference game at Canyons. Larry Allbritton led Canyons (7-12, 0-2) with 26 
points and fellow forward Aaron Clark scored 20. Canyons' Nick Sanderson scored 
21. Cal Poly SLO 80, Master's 74 -- Cal Poly had a 76-71 lead in the last four 
minutes and held on. 
</P>
</TEXT>
