<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEWITZKY'S DECADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Notwithstanding limitations of space, both Lewis Segal's and Martin 
Bernheimer's Dec. 26 retrospectives on dance in the '80s made a serious 
omission. 
</P>
<P>
Bella Lewitzky's accomplishments in the '80s (20th company anniversary, 
acclaimed international premieres, etc.) are noteworthy for dance historians, 
but L.A.'s media particularly should recognize -- indeed, highlight her 
continued success these 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN KEEPERS and AMY ERNST, Hermosa Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
