<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DIGGERS, PLANTERS: GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
* Check out the ornamental cousins of two winter vegetables by asking for 
flowering kale or cabbage. 
</P>
<P>
Their intensely colored rosettes will brighten winter flower beds. 
</P>
<P>
* Look up two popular flowering shrubs in the garden center: azaleas and 
camellias. 
</P>
<P>
* Put in your first planting of gladiolus this month and follow it up with 
additional plantings at 15-day intervals to extend their blooming period. 
</P>
<P>
* For a delightful ground cover in the shadier part of your lawn, don't forget 
to plant forget-me-nots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
