SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EL CAJON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An El Cajon man pleaded guilty Friday to child molestation involving the use of 
an electrical cord around the throat of an 8-year-old Cub Scout. 
</P>
<P>
Jerry Frazier, 21, who recently was a distribution manager for The Wall Street 
Journal, pleaded guilty just as his preliminary hearing was about to start. 
</P>
<P>
Frazier admitted to fondling the genitals of the Cub Scout, who told his 
parents of the incident after Frazier had taken him to his house after a Scout 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
Frazier admitted to two allegations, that he kidnaped the victim and used a 
deadly weapon, the electrical cord, during the crime. 
</P>
<P>
"It was wrapped around the child's throat," causing the boy to lose 
consciousness, Deputy Dist. Atty. Harry Elias said. 
</P>
<P>
Frazier could receive a maximum sentence of 19 years in state prison if 
convicted.. 
</P>
<P>
Sentencing was set for April 5. 
</P>
