<P>
COLORADO; 
</P>
<P>
GUILTY PLEA ENDS HUD THEFT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former accountant for the Department of Housing and Urban Development pleaded 
guilty to one count of theft for allegedly embezzling $1 million from the 
federal government. Douglas R. Turner, 38, entered the plea in U.S. District 
Court in Denver as part of an agreement that called for three other theft 
counts to be dropped. Prosecutors say Turner used a government computer to 
transfer about $1 million from the HUD Section 8 rent-subsidy program to the 
bank account of a real estate company he owned. 
</P>
