<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOULD-BE ROBBER LEAVES BOGUS BOMB IN BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fake bomb left on a desk by a would-be robber forced the evacuation Friday of 
about 20 people from a Security Pacific National Bank branch in Hollywood, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Dressed casually in a sport coat and polo shirt, a man entered the bank in the 
7600 block of Sunset Boulevard about 2 p.m. and asked for a $35,000 loan. 
</P>
<P>
After discussing the loan for a half hour with a bank employee, the man pulled 
out a red box and threatened to blow up the bank unless he got the money, said 
Detective Lt. Bob Ruchhoft. 
</P>
<P>
The man fled when the employee went to the bank vault. No money was taken and 
employees were allowed to return in about an hour. Police found crumpled 
newspapers in the box. 
</P>
</TEXT>
