<P>
Guidelines for Au Pair Families 
</P>
<P>
Qualifications: Family must undergo screening process to determine financial 
capability and social suitability. Family must have extra bedroom in home. 
</P>
<P>
Duties: Child-care responsibilities cannot exceed 45 hours a week, or nine 
hours a day. No heavy housework can be required. 
</P>
<P>
Time off: One weekend off per month and one and a half days off per week. 
</P>
<P>
Compensation: Besides the up-front cost of air fare and counseling services, 
family provides room and board, weekly stipend of $100 and up to $300 for 
education. 
</P>
<P>
Social: Since program is based on cultural exchange, family should include au 
pair in family activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
